Rating: 4
Hi, I'm indian and have been cooking and eating dal all my life. It is not supposed to be particularly spiced...it is supposed to be somewhat mild compared to curry and stereotypical Indian food. It is meant to be mixed thoroughly into rice (not Basmati but regular thick sticky rice) and eaten as comfort food with a drizzling of butter. It is not meant to be elegant, flashy, or particularly "spicy." The most traditional way to eat dal is simply to steam the lentils with rice and salt and pepper. So that is probably why some people were disappointed in the simplicity of this recipe. If you're looking to be comforted, look no further, but if you're easily bored, make something else. This recipe is good, just be generous with the bay leaves (saute in hot oil with poppy seeds before adding garlic and onion).

