Rating: 3
I just made this recipe, and wanted to weigh in with my thoughts. I went to India for the first time a couple of months ago. While that doesn't make me an authority on what tastes good, or on Indian food for that matter, I will say this: I had many different dals in India. Some don't have coconut; some do. Some have heavy cream. Some are spicy; some are not. Some are watery, and some are not. I would have to say that there is no single "right" way to make dal. This particular recipe is on the less-spicy, more-watery end of the spectrum. It is well within the bounds of what I experienced in India. Think of it as a side dish--something to make your rice more exciting. It would not be my ideal stand-alone dal, because of its austerity. But it would go nicely with a complex, spicy meat dish, for example. When I made it, I used clarified butter instead of vegetable oil. This is a good modification. I also recommend using white pepper instead of black pepper, for asthetic reasons.

