Rating: 0
I just wanted to post the recipe i use for dal my friend taught me. boil lentils in 1 teas salt and 1-2 t tumeric. cook until soft and tender in a pan, heat a few T of oil with mustard seeds and whole dried chilis. wait until seeds have popped (cover the pan by the way). add some chopped onion, garlic and ginger. as onions become cooked, add 1-2 teaspoons of garam masala, curry powder and 1/2-1 t of crushed dried chili. heat until aromatic. add to cooked lentils and heat for 2-5 minutes. can add tomatoes, a teaspoon of butter to finish, a touch of cream. it is a very flexible recipe.

