Rating: 0
This dish is actually what is know in the Indo-Pak subconinent as a Tarka dal. The frying of the browned onions and garlic should be done after the lentils are made and immediatediately pour on top of lentils hot when done frying and mix. The lentils are definitely not pureed. As a purist, curry powder is not something that one just dumps in everything, when you see "indian" in the title of the recipe. "Curry" is overused and misunderstood, and you are leaving all your food to have that same "curry" flavor. Subcontinent cooking is a subtle blend of different spices for different dishes, and about enjoying that difference. Everything indian does not have 5 million spices in it. This dish is more about enjoying the taste of the carmelized onions and garlic, and it often tastes better the next day.

