well, to be perfectly honest, I've never made this specific recipe. but having found my favorite-ever comfort food at epicurious, i can't help but comment. serve this with basmati rice and sauteed, lightly spiced potatoes -- mmmmm!!!!! it's my favorite meal ever, one my mom makes for my last meal whenever i'm back home. my mom's is different in a few ways. she uses fresh ginger, added directly to the lentils. and a more traditional way of doing the spices is to fry them separately. my mom uses whole cumin, turmeric, garlic (no onion, black mustard seed, dried red chiles. fry these until the cumin seeds start turning pink, and the mustard seeds start popping. add that lentils as they're boiling (no need to wait till the end). i would also bump up the spice amounts. and a squeeze of lemon or lime juice at the end also adds a delicious dimension of flavor. finally, it's totally unnecessary to use the blender. all that gives you is more cleaning up to do. just cook it a little longer for a mushier texture.

